<author><name><![CDATA[tokumaru]]></name></author>
<updated>2008-07-23T22:17:02-07:00</updated>
<published>2008-07-23T22:17:02-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4247&amp;p=35226#p35226</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4247&amp;p=35226#p35226"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[blarg's tutorial (ca65 examples thread) question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4247&amp;p=35226#p35226"><![CDATA[
Yeah, they call those bits "Base nametable address", which isn't wrong. Just think about the width of a screen. It's 256 pixels wide, so The X scroll register (which is 8 bits wide) can address any of those pixels. Now, when there are 2 screens/nametables in a row, the total width is 512 pixels, which means you need 1 extra bit (for a total of 9) in order to address any pixel in that area. So, you can think of this bit as a "nametable selection bit" (because it indicates if the pixel you want is at the left side or at the right side), or as a 9th bit of the scroll value, for a total of 512 pixels.<br /><br />As a programmer of scrolling games, I like to think of those bits as the 9th bits of each scroll coordinate. Authors of non-scrolling games might be more comfortable referring to them as "nametable selection bits", because they just use them to pick 1 of 4 possible nametables at a time.<br /><br />About learning how to program games, that's kinda hard... I can't really suggest someone does what I did, because I started back in the DOS days, and that's just not practical at all these days. Maybe one of those Flash Game Programming books... I recently downloaded one about ActionScript 3 games that covered many of the basic principles of a game. And Flash is really great to just get things going quickly.<br /><br />Once you have the general idea of how a game works, you might see more clearly how all of that PPU and 6502 information can be put together to form something decent.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed Jul 23, 2008 10:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
