<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4247&amp;p=35223#p35223"><![CDATA[
Technical documents don't usually tell you how to efficiently intereact with the hardware or provide any examples of that, they simply tell how the hardware will react to certain things, simply stating the facts. This is what makes it so difficult for a newbie to make any sense out of them. This is also the reason why it is impossible to make a game just from reading technical documents.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed Jul 23, 2008 9:26 pm</p><hr />
