Hmmm... I'm not sure what you mean by that since the msb of the PPUCTRL ($2000) is the NMI set bit.  <br /><br />How is it related to the scroll and why would you want to set it every time you scroll?  This is what I'm curious about right now.<br /><br />Just for other people that may read this thread, the constants used in this example are:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">PPUCTRL   = $2000<br />PPUMASK   = $2001<br />PPUSCROLL = $2005<br /><br />PPUCTRL_NMI = %10000000<br /></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3559">Banshaku</a> — Wed Jul 23, 2008 8:08 am</p><hr />
